Issue #1: Build an Intelligent Twitter/X Financial Sentiment & Signal Monitor
Body: 1. Objective
Develop a resilient, automated data ingestion pipeline using headless browser automation to monitor high-profile Twitter/X accounts for US stock investment signals. The focus is on bypassing anti-scraping measures to fetch real-time, unstructured social data for subsequent AI sentiment analysis.

2. Proposed Technical Stack
Language: Python 3.11+

Browser Automation: Playwright (Preferred for speed/stealth) or Selenium (if specific legacy extensions are required).

Stealth & Resilience: * Stealth Plugin: Implement playwright-stealth or equivalent to minimize bot detection.

Proxy Management: Integration with a residential proxy service to rotate IPs and prevent bans.

User-Agent Rotation: Dynamic rotation of valid headers/fingerprints.

AI/Analysis: LLM (OpenAI API or local Ollama model) to process content after extraction.

Storage: PostgreSQL (for relational data) + ChromaDB (for vector search on historical tweets).

3. Core Functional Requirements
Dynamic Rendering: The browser must handle JavaScript-heavy rendering, as X/Twitter loads content dynamically.

Background Request Interception: Configure the scraper to intercept GraphQL/XHR background requests to capture clean JSON responses instead of parsing raw DOM elements (highly recommended for stability).

Rate Limiting & Throttling: Implement randomized human-like delays (time.sleep(random.uniform(2, 5))) between actions.

Session Persistence: Ability to save/load authentication cookies (via a "burner" account) to minimize login prompts and reduce trigger frequency.

4. Implementation Strategy (The "Stealth" Protocol)
No Hardcoded Selectors: Since X frequently updates CSS classes, the scraper should rely on stable attributes (like data-testid) or AI-based extraction (e.g., using Stagehand or ScrapeGraphAI primitives) to locate tweet content.

Error Handling: Robust retry logic with exponential backoff for 429 (Rate Limit) or 403 (Forbidden) errors.

Logging & Alerts: Log every failed attempt. Send a Telegram/Discord alert if the scraper is blocked so we can manually intervene or update cookies.

5. Acceptance Criteria
Successfully fetch the "Latest" feed from a list of 20+ tracked handles without being logged out.

Pipeline is capable of running headless (without a GUI) on a server/container (e.g., Docker/AWS EC2).

Scraper successfully exports structured data: [Timestamp, Author, Tweet_Text, Tickers_Detected, Media_URL].
